@ottobackwards If I read the JIRA correctly " , " is supposed to stay valid for this PR, is that right? If that's the case then LGTM +1

I read through every use of it in the framework to see what the impact would be. The only uses of the validator in the framework have trimEntries and excludeEmptyEntries set to true. And most uses (CaptureChangeMySQL, LivySessionController, DBCPConnectionPool, AbstractAzureLogAnalyticsReportingTask/AzureLogAnalyticsReportingTask) re-validate or re-split and re-validate before using the value.

Only JMSConnectionFactoryProvider and JndiJmsConnectionFactoryProvider don't re-validate.

I have a simple flow which uses `InvokeHttp` with a `StandardRestrictedSSLContextService` to connect to https://nifi.apache.org/download.html and retrieve the page content. 

@natural please test this against your Elasticsearch instance as well. 

[flow_20200214-192703_NIFI-6927-InvokeHTTP-SSL.xml.gz](https://github.com/apache/nifi/files/4207714/flow_20200214-192703_NIFI-6927-InvokeHTTP-SSL.xml.gz)

@pvillard31 Thanks for the heads-up.
I updated google-auth-library-oauth2-http in the services-api-nar to the same version as in the processors-nar which is 0.18.0.
Please note that the latest google-cloud-bom version (0.122.2-alpha) leads to a build error in NiFi (details in [NIFI-7143](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NIFI-7143?focusedCommentId=17038533&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-17038533)). That's why I upgraded to a recent (0.120.2-alpha), but not the latest version.
